\begin_layout Standard
The purpose of this bachelor project is to design and implement an Android
 application that uses location data obtained with hardware sensors to provide
 navigation instructions to the user.
 The navigation instructions will guide the user to a certain location by
 manipulating a binarual sound differently depending on the user's direction
 to the location.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The guided sound will be implemented in a game to encourage running, thus
 intending to prevent the sedentary in the society of the present time.
 Apart from making running into a more fun experience the application will
 register running activity and present statistics.
 To enhance the usability of the application it will have a straight forward
 graphical user interface that is easy to understand.
 
\end_layout

